The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, June 29, 2004 				 Bus brutes held
																								Midnapore, June 28: The driver and conductor of the bus from which Sunil Mahato was thrown out on Midnapore-Purulia Road, 150 km from Calcutta, and who teased his wife have been caught.																								Rabindra Bag and Gour Pain were arrested from Kharagpur. Mahato died and his wife jumped out of the bus in which Bag and Pain were joined by two others in teasing her. Police said the other duo will be arrested soon.
